formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. Out of 390 units, the Lender has already issued NOC for 159 units and hence 231 units are still under encumbrance with such lender.
2. The promoter has taken line of credit (LOC) facility to part finance this project. This LOC operates as overdraft facility wherein numerous disbursements are being availed and numerous repayments are being made. There are no fixed amount of installments for repayment of this LOC as per sanctioned terms. 
3. In case of  16 units, Amount received is more than 10% of Unit Amount. Out of such 16 units, 15 units were booked before RERA came into force (i.e. Before 01/05/2017) and other 1 is post RERA but before RERA Registration. As explained to us by the Promoter, they already have approached those Allottees via emails, phone calls etc to execute Registration of Agreement for Sale with such Allottees however, they have not turned up so far. Promoter is still perusing to complete pending execution. 
4. RERA carpet area is taken as given by the management/promoter developer.
5. Estimated Sale value (unit wise) for Unbooked units is taken as given by the management/promoter developer.
6. RERA carpet area stated above, excludes area of Balcony/Varandah, washyard & Open terrace.
7. Admin, General, Marketing & Selling Expenses are excluded.
8. Online module/system for filing Form-3 doesn't permit actual cost incurred & paid when the same is higher than the estimated cost. Hence, actual cost incurred & paid is stated upto the estimated cost.
